Seasonal farmworkers in the Western Cape’s Winelands are demanding better salaries and a review of their working conditions. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. #DStv403 KLAPMUTS - Seasonal farmworkers in the Western Cape’s Winelands are demanding better salaries and a review of their working conditions. They say the farms they work on ignore labour laws. READ: Ceres healthcare workers and residents protest for better care Social justice organisation, Women on Farms Project, took to the streets this week to highlight their plight. They handed over a set of demands to Distell Wine Producers. * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.